        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 7:04PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 704 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mimosa, or 9 miles southwest of Mount Ida, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Ida...                      Norman...
Oden...                           Mauldin...
Mimosa...                         Black Springs...
Silver...                         Fancyhill...
Pencil Bluff...                   Hopper...
Caddo Gap...                      Hurricane Grove...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
